        <section class="intro">
            <p>The <strong>Weather Prediction Model Intercomparison Project (WP-MIP)</strong> aims to identify the strengths and weaknesses of AI, hybrid, and physical numerical weather prediction models. The <a href="https://www.wcrp-esmo.org/activities/wp-mip">WP-MIP website</a> provides background about the project and links to all associated resources.</p>

            <p>This is the landing pad for the WP-MIP forecast archive, hosted by Environment and Climate Change Canada (ECCC). The data stored in this archive has been submitted by contributing institutions following WP-MIP protocols. The core protocol requires that contributors provide 10-day global deterministic forecasts on a common 0.25-deg global grid. Forecasts are initialized every three days throughout 2024, beginning with 0000 UCT 1 January 2024.</p>

            <div class="info-box">
                <p><strong>Contribution Streams:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Own Initial Conditions (OIC):</strong> Forecasts initialized using datasets generated by the contributing centre (or other centres if they do not generate their own).</li>
                    <li><strong>Same Initial Conditions (SIC):</strong> Forecasts initialized from operational European Centre for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts (ECMWF) analyses.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

