        <section class="instructions">
            <h3>Retrieving WP-MIP Forecasts</h3>
            <p>For an interactive look at available WP-MIP data, use the links above. Alternatively, you can <a href="WP-MIP">browse the archive directory</a> directly. These methods are useful for downloading a small number of files.</p>

            <p>To download larger volumes of data, use the <code>wget</code> application. Below is an example to retrieve all 500 hPa geopotential height forecasts from the IFS integrations submitted by ECMWF:</p>

            <div class="code-block">
                <pre>wget -e robots=off -nd -r --no-parent -A "*_500*.grib2" http://hpfx.collab.science.gc.ca/~swpm001/WP-MIP/forecasts/oic/ecmf/pm_00/gh/</pre>
            </div>
            
            <p class="note"><em>Note: Modify the wildcards in the file name and path to target specific data.</em></p>
